<br>
So, the harm you cause by infringing on someone else's fun is perfectly okay, but when someone else wants what was promised to FV when the server opened, if that might infringe on your advancing, your fun, then it's wrong.<br>
<br>
I sent my letters.  I am my own voice.  I won't let your fun infringe on mine.  However, if it continues to do escalate like this, infringing on the &quot;fun&quot; of some to satisfy the &quot;fun&quot; of the ubers, well, then I will take my fun elsewhere and you can have all the &quot;fun&quot; you want.<br>
<br>
I don't care who said thing about Nek/Lake Rathe, it was condescending and was echoing, in sentiment, what Witherweaver, a representative of his guild, was saying.  No one but them deserves an iota of consideration because.. well.. because they can.<br>
<br>
Let me give you a clue there.  We (the not so uber) get pissed when a place we want to go and have done as much due dilligence as possible to make sure no one else is planning to go there is trampled on by the &quot;ubers&quot; out for a day of &quot;fun&quot;.  This will increase with the transfers.  Yes, it is just competition and why should any consideration be given to anyone &quot;less&quot; than you.<br>
